#To modify the changes made on the vs code  use this
open termunal--> git init--> git status-->

there are 4things in it 
1] untracked :: new files that git doesnt yet track
2] modified :: changed
3] staged :: file is ready to be  committed
4] unmodified :: no changes made
change(modified -->add-->commit)   newfile-->untracked-->staged-->unchanged

#Things to do it on vs code if we change or modified that is auto done github  steps follow below
#ADD AND COMMIT
add:: adds new or changed files in your working directory to the git staging area
git add<file name>
to  add all files:: git add .

commit:: it is the record of change
git commit -m "some message"

PUSH COMMAND:: upload local repo content to remote repo
git push origin main

git remote add origin https://github.com/abhisandeep15/demo2
gcloneit  origin master

















































